error.signature: Error: Unable to find any artifacts for the associated workflow
error.regex: (?:Unable to find any artifacts|Artifact not found|No artifacts found|download-artifact.*not found)

verdict.summary: A GitHub Actions job attempts to download an artifact that was not uploaded by a previous job or workflow run. Common causes include artifact name mismatches, expired artifacts, or upload failures in prior jobs.

dead_ends.action: Increase artifact retention days expecting it to fix missing artifacts
dead_ends.why_fails: Retention only applies to existing artifacts; if the artifact was never uploaded, extending retention has no effect

dead_ends.action: Re-run only the download job without re-running the upload job
dead_ends.why_fails: The artifact must exist before it can be downloaded; re-running only the consumer job does not recreate the artifact

workarounds.action: Ensure artifact names match exactly between upload-artifact and download-artifact steps
workarounds.how: Verify the 'name' parameter in actions/upload-artifact matches the 'name' parameter in actions/download-artifact exactly, including case sensitivity

workarounds.action: Add needs: dependency to ensure upload job completes before download job starts
workarounds.how: Add 'needs: [build-job]' to the job that downloads artifacts, ensuring the upload job runs first. Also verify the upload step is not skipped by conditionals

leads_to.condition: When missing build artifacts cause deployment to fail and rollback is attempted

preceded_by.condition: When Docker build failure prevents artifact upload

frequently_confused_with.distinction: Artifact not found refers to build outputs shared between jobs; cache miss refers to dependency caching for faster builds
